Plot: An insecure man has his dimwitted actor friend pose as his mentally challenged brother in order to get to know a beautiful co-worker who has a mentally challenged sister.

This is not just a B-movie, it's a &quot;no-budget-movie&quot; - litterally! It's a bunch of unemployed actors with a simple camera and a good idea for a comedy - nothing else!
The result is nothing less than a good movie in doubtable quality, that has thrilled audiences at film festivals around the country. If you are a true movie lover, who cares more about plot and acting than looks and quality, you will appreciate this one.

4.7 score on IMDB - well done for a movie with no budget.
